  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Genealogy from Adam'
      title: Genealogy from Adam
      number: 1
      content: '  Adam [his genealogical line], Seth, Enosh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Noah, [and his sons] Shem, Ham, and Japheth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sons (descendants) of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal,
        Meshech, and Tiras. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Diphath, and Togarmah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Rodanim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Ham: Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raama, and Sabteca. The sons
        of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Cush became the father of Nimrod; he began to be a mighty one upon
        the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Mizraim became the father of the people of Lud, Anam, Lehab, Naphtuh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Pathrus, and Casluh, from whom came the Philistines, and Caphtor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Canaan became the father of Sidon his firstborn, and Heth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the Jebusites, Amorites, Girgashites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Hivites, Arkites, Sinites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Arvadites, Zemarites, and Hamathites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, Aram, Uz, Hul, Gether,
        and Meshech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Arpachshad became the father of Shelah, and Shelah became the father
        of Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "To Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg, because
        in his days [the population of] the earth was divided [according to its languages],
        and his brother\u2019s name was Joktan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Joktan became the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Ebal, Abimael, Sheba, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Shem [his genealogical line], Arpachshad, Shelah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Eber, Peleg, Reu, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Serug, Nahor, Terah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Descendants of Abraham'
      title: Descendants of Abraham
      number: 27
      content: 'Abram, the same as Abraham.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Abraham: Isaac [by his wife Sarah] and Ishmael [by Hagar
        her maid]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'These are their descendants: The firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth;
        then Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now the sons of Keturah, Abraham\u2019s concubine: she gave birth
        to Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. The sons of Jokshan:
        Sheba and Dedan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Midian: Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All
        these are the sons [and grandsons] of Keturah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Abraham became the father of Isaac. The sons of Isaac: Esau and Israel
        (Jacob). '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of Esau: Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The sons of Eliphaz: Teman, Omar, Zephi, Gatam, Kenaz, Timna, and
        Amalek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The sons of Seir: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer, and
        Dishan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "The sons of Lotan: Hori and Homam; and Timna was Lotan\u2019s sister. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The sons of Shobal: Alian, Manahath, Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. The
        sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The son of Anah: Dishon. The sons of Dishon: Hamran, Eshban, Ithran,
        and Cheran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Jaakan. The sons of Dishan:
        Uz and Aran.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any king
        reigned over the sons (descendants) of Israel (Jacob): Bela the son of Beor;
        the name of his city was Dinhabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'When Bela died, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah became king in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'When Jobab died, Husham of the land of the Temanites became king
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'When Husham died, Hadad [I of Edom] the son of Bedad, who defeated
        Midian in the field of Moab, became king in his place; the name of his city
        was Avith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'When Hadad [I] died, Samlah of Masrekah became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'When Samlah died, Shaul of Rehoboth on the River [Euphrates] became
        king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'When Shaul died, Baal-hanan the son of Achbor became king in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "When Baal-hanan died, Hadad [II] became king in his place; the name
        of his city was Pai; his wife\u2019s name was Mehetabel daughter of Matred,
        the daughter of Mezahab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Hadad died also.  The chiefs of Edom were: chiefs Timna, Aliah, Jetheth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: Magdiel, and Iram. These are the chiefs of Edom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Genealogy: Twelve Sons of Jacob (Israel)'
      title: 'Genealogy: Twelve Sons of Jacob (Israel)'
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the sons of Israel: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar,
        Zebulun, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The sons of Judah: Er, Onan, and Shelah; the three were born to him
        by Shua\u2019s daughter the Canaanitess. Er, Judah\u2019s eldest, was evil
        in the Lord\u2019s sight, and He put him to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Tamar, Judah\u2019s daughter-in-law, bore him Perez and Zerah. Judah\u2019s
        sons were five in all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sons of Perez: Hezron and Hamul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The sons of Zerah: Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Dara\u2014five
        in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The son of Carmi: Achar, the troubler of Israel, who violated the
        ban [by taking things from Jericho that had been banned]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Genealogy of David'
      title: Genealogy of David
      number: 8
      content: 'The son of Ethan: Azariah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Hezron who were born to him: Jerahmeel, Ram, and Chelubai
        [that is, Caleb]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Ram became the father of Amminadab, and Amminadab became the father
        of Nahshon, leader of the sons of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Nahshon became the father of Salma, Salma became the father of Boaz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Boaz became the father of Obed, and Obed became the father of Jesse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jesse became the father of Eliab his firstborn, Abinadab the second,
        Shimea the third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ozem the sixth, David the seventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Their sisters were Zeruiah and Abigail. The sons of Zeruiah: Abishai,
        Joab, and Asahel, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Abigail gave birth to Amasa, and the father of Amasa was Jether the
        Ishmaelite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Caleb the son of Hezron had sons by his wife Azubah and by Jerioth.
        Azubah\u2019s sons were: Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Azubah died, and Caleb married Ephrath, who bore him Hur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Hur became the father of Uri, and Uri became the father of Bezalel
        [the skillful craftsman who made the furnishings of the tabernacle].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Later, when Hezron was sixty years old, he married the daughter of
        Machir the father of Gilead, and she bore him Segub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Segub became the father of Jair, who [later] had twenty-three cities
        in the land of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But Geshur and Aram took from them Havvoth-jair, with Kenath and
        its villages, sixty towns in all. All these were the sons (descendants) of
        Machir, the father of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "After Hezron died in Caleb-ephrathah, Abijah, Hezron\u2019s wife,
        bore him Ashhur the father of Tekoa.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron: Ram the firstborn,
        Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Jerahmeel had another wife, named Atarah; she was the mother of Onam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerahmeel were: Maaz, Jamin, and
        Eker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Onam: Shammai and Jada. The sons of Shammai: Nadab and
        Abishur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The name of Abishur\u2019s wife was Abihail; she bore him Ahban and
        Molid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The sons of Nadab: Seled and Appaim. Seled died childless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The son of Appaim: Ishi. The son of Ishi: Sheshan. The son of Sheshan:
        Ahlai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The sons of Jada the brother of Shammai: Jether and Jonathan. Jether
        died childless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Jonathan: Peleth and Zaza. These were the sons (descendants)
        of Jerahmeel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Sheshan had no sons\u2014only daughters. But Sheshan had a servant,
        an Egyptian, whose name was Jarha. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant as a wife; she
        bore him Attai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Attai became the father of Nathan, and Nathan became the father of
        Zabad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zabad became the father of Ephlal, and Ephlal became the father of
        Obed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Obed became the father of Jehu, and Jehu became the father of Azariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Azariah became the father of Helez, and Helez became the father of
        Eleasah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Eleasah became the father of Sismai, and Sismai became the father
        of Shallum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Shallum became the father of Jekamiah, and Jekamiah became the father
        of Elishama.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sons of Caleb, the brother of Jerahmeel: Mesha his firstborn
        was the father of Ziph; and his son Mareshah was the father of Hebron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The sons of Hebron: Korah, Tappuah, Rekem, and Shema. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Shema became the father of Raham, the father of Jorkeam. And Rekem
        became the father of Shammai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The son of Shammai was Maon; Maon became the father of Bethzur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Ephah, Caleb\u2019s concubine, gave birth to Haran, Moza, and Gazez;
        Haran became the father of Gazez. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The sons of Jahdai: Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah, and Shaaph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Maacah, Caleb\u2019s concubine, gave birth to Sheber and Tirhanah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'She also bore Shaaph the father of Madmannah and Sheva the father
        of Machbena and of Gibea; and the daughter of Caleb was Achsah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'These were the sons (descendants) of Caleb.  The sons of Hur, the
        firstborn of Ephrathah: Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Salma the father of Bethlehem and Hareph the father of Beth-gader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim had [other] sons (descendants):
        Haroeh, half of the Manahathites [in Judah], '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'and the families of Kiriath-jearim: the Ithrites, Puthites, Shumathites,
        and Mishraites. From these came the Zorathites and the Eshtaolites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The sons (descendants) of Salma: Bethlehem, the Netophathites, Atroth-beth-joab,
        and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'The families of scribes who lived at Jabez: the Tirathites, Shimeathites,
        and Sucathites. These are the Kenites who came from Hammath, the father of
        the house of Rechab.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Family of David'
      title: Family of David
      number: 1
      content: '  These were the sons of David who were born to him in Hebron: the
        firstborn was Amnon, by Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; second, Daniel (Chileab),
        by Abigail the Carmelitess; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'third, Absalom the son of Maacah, daughter of Talmai king of Geshur;
        fourth, Adonijah, the son of Haggith; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'fifth, Shephatiah, by Abital; sixth, Ithream, by his wife Eglah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These six were born to David in Hebron; he reigned there seven years
        and six months, and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "These were born to David in Jerusalem: Shimea (Shammua), Shobab,
        Nathan, Solomon\u2014four by Bath-shua (Bathsheba) daughter of Ammiel (Eliam); "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'then Ibhar, Elishama (Elishua), Eliphelet (Elpelet), '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Elishama, Eliada (Beeliada), and Eliphelet\u2014nine in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All these were the sons of David, besides the sons of the concubines;
        and Tamar was their sister.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Solomon\u2019s son was Rehoboam. Abijah was his son, Asa his son,
        Jehoshaphat his son, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Joram (Jehoram) his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Amon his son, Josiah his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Josiah: firstborn, Johanan; second, Jehoiakim (Eliakim);
        third, Zedekiah; fourth, Shallum (Jehoahaz). '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons (descendants) of Jehoiakim: Jehoiachin (Jeconiah) his son,
        Zedekiah his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons (descendants) of Jehoiachin (Jeconiah) the prisoner: Shealtiel
        his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Malchiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama and Nedabiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Pedaiah: Zerubbabel and Shimei. The sons of Zerubbabel:
        Meshullam and Hananiah, and Shelomith was their sister; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and Hashubah, Ohel, Berechiah, Hasadiah, and Jushab-hesed\u2014five
        in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Hananiah: Pelatiah and Jeshaiah, the sons of Rephaiah,
        the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, the sons of Shecaniah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The sons (descendants) of Shecaniah: Shemaiah. The sons of Shemaiah:
        Hattush, Igal, Bariah, Neariah, and Shaphat\u2014six in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The sons of Neariah: Elioenai, Hizkiah, and Azrikam\u2014three in
        all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The sons of Elioenai: Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan,
        Delaiah, and Anani\u2014seven in all."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Judah'
      title: Descendants of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The sons of Judah: Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur, and Shobal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Reaiah the son of Shobal became the father of Jahath, and Jahath
        became the father of Ahumai and Lahad. These were the families of the Zorathites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'These were the sons of Etam: Jezreel, Ishma, and Idbash; and the
        name of their sister was Hazzelelponi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Penuel was the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah. These
        were the sons of Hur, the eldest of Ephrathah (Ephrath), the father of Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ashhur, the father of Tekoa, had two wives, Helah and Naarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni and Haahashtari. These were
        Naarah\u2019s sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Helah: Zereth, Izhar, and Ethnan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Koz fathered Anub, Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of
        Harum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jabez was more honorable than his brothers; but his mother named
        him Jabez, saying, \u201CBecause I gave birth to him in pain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jabez cried out to the God of Israel, saying, \u201COh that You would
        indeed bless me and enlarge my border [property], and that Your hand would
        be with me, and You would keep me from evil so that it does not hurt me!\u201D
        And God granted his request.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Chelub the brother of Shuhah became the father of Mehir, the father
        of Eshton. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Eshton became the father of Beth-rapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah the
        father of Ir-nahash. These are the men of Recah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Kenaz: Othniel and Seraiah. The sons of Othniel: Hathath
        and Meonothai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Meonothai became the father of Ophrah, and Seraiah became the father
        of Joab the father of Ge-harashim [the Valley of Craftsmen, so named] because
        they were craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The sons of Caleb [Joshua\u2019s companion] the son of Jephunneh:
        Iru, Elah, and Naam. The son of Elah: Kenaz. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Jehallelel: Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Ezrah: Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon. These are the
        sons of Bithia daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered took: she conceived and gave
        birth to Miriam, Shammai, and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Mered\u2019s Jewish wife gave birth to Jered the father of Gedor,
        Heber the father of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of the wife of Hodiah, the sister of Naham, were: the fathers
        of Keilah the Garmite and Eshtemoa the Maacathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Shimon: Amnon, Rinnah, Benhanan, and Tilon. The sons
        of Ishi: Zoheth and Ben-zoheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Shelah son of Judah: Er the father of Lecah and Laadah
        the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house of the linen workers
        at Beth-ashbea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and Jokim, the men of Cozeba, Joash, and Saraph, who ruled in Moab,
        and Jashubi-lehem. These are ancient words (genealogical records). '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Descendants of Simeon'
      title: Descendants of Simeon
      number: 23
      content: 'These were the potters and those who lived [among plantations and
        hedges] at Netaim and Gederah; they lived there with the king for his work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Simeon: Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, and Shaul; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Shallum was Shaul\u2019s son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The sons of Mishma: Hammuel his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers did not
        have many sons, neither did all their family multiply like the sons of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They lived at Beersheba, Moladah, Hazar-shual, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Bilhah, Ezem, Tolad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susim, Beth-biri, and at Shaaraim. These were
        their cities until the reign of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "These were their villages: Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Tochen, and Ashan\u2014five
        cities\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'and all their villages that were around these towns as far as Baal.
        These were their settlements, and they have their genealogical record.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Meshobab, Jamlech, Joshah the son of Amaziah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Joel, Jehu the son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'also Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Ziza the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the
        son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "these mentioned by name were leaders in their families; and their
        fathers\u2019 houses increased greatly [so they needed more land]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So they journeyed to the entrance of Gedor, to the east side of the
        valley, to seek pasture for their flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'They found rich, good pasture, and the [cleared] land was wide, quiet,
        and peaceful; for those who had lived there previously came from Ham [and
        had left it a better place for those who came after them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'These, registered by name, came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah,
        and they attacked their tents and the Meunites (foreigners) who were found
        there, and utterly destroyed them to this day; and they settled in their
        place, because there was pasture there for their flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'From them, from the sons of Simeon, five hundred men went to Mount
        Seir, with Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi, as
        their leaders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: They destroyed the remnant of the Amalekites who escaped, and they
        have lived there to this day (the date of this writing).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Reuben'
      title: Descendants of Reuben
      number: 1
      content: "  Now [we come to] the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel\u2014for
        Reuben was the eldest, but because he defiled his father\u2019s bed [with
        Bilhah his father\u2019s concubine], his birthright was given to [Manasseh
        and Ephraim] the sons of Joseph [the favorite] son of Israel, so that he
        is not enrolled in the genealogy according to the birthright. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Though Judah prevailed over his brothers, and from him came [David]
        the leader [and eventually the Messiah], yet the birthright was Joseph\u2019s\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron,
        and Carmi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Joel: Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Beerah his son, whom Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria carried away
        into exile; he was a leader of the tribe of Reuben. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And his brothers (relatives) by their families, in the genealogy
        of their generations, were the chief Jeiel, and Zechariah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who lived
        in Aroer as far as Nebo and Baal-meon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'To the east Bela settled as far as the entrance into the desert from
        the river Euphrates, because their cattle had multiplied in the land of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Descendants of Gad'
      title: Descendants of Gad
      number: 10
      content: 'In the days of King Saul they made war with the Hagrites, who fell
        by their hands; and they lived in their tents throughout all the land east
        of Gilead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Gad lived opposite them in the land of Bashan, as far
        as Salecah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Joel was the chief, Shapham the second, then Janai and Shaphat in
        Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Their relatives from the households of their fathers: Michael, Meshullam,
        Sheba, Jorai, Jacan, Zia, and Eber\u2014seven in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These were the sons of Abihail the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah,
        the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo,
        the son of Buz; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, was chief in their fathers\u2019
        households. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They lived in Gilead, in Bashan and in its towns, and in all the
        [surrounding] pasture lands of Sharon, as far as their borders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All these were enrolled in the genealogies in the days of Jotham
        king of Judah and in the days of Jeroboam [II] king of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The sons of Reuben, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh\u2014valiant
        men able to bear shield and sword, and to shoot with the bow, and skillful
        in war\u2014were 44,760 who went to war. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And these Israelites, [on the east side of the Jordan River] made
        war with the Hagrites [a tribe of northern Arabia], Jetur, Naphish, and Nodab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They were given help against them, and the Hagrites were handed over
        to them, and all who were allied with them; for they cried out to God [for
        help] in the battle; and He granted their entreaty because they relied on
        and trusted in Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'These Israelites took away their livestock: their 50,000 camels,
        and 250,000 sheep, and 2,000 donkeys; and 100,000 people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Descendants of Manasseh'
      title: Descendants of Manasseh
      number: 22
      content: 'For a great number fell mortally wounded, because the battle was
        of God. And these Israelites settled in their territory until the exile [by
        Assyria more than five centuries later].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now the sons (people) of the half-tribe of Manasseh lived in the
        land; their settlements spread from Bashan to Baal-hermon and Senir and Mount
        Hermon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "These were the heads of their fathers\u2019 households: Epher, Ishi,
        Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, warriors of valor [willing
        and able to encounter danger], famous men, and heads of the households of
        their fathers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But they acted treacherously against the God of their fathers and
        played the prostitute with the gods of the peoples of the land, whom God
        had destroyed before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul, king of Assyria,
        [that is,] the spirit of Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria, and he carried
        them away into exile\u2014the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh\u2014and brought them to Halah, Habor, Hara, and the river Gozan,
        [where they remain] to this day."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Genealogy: The Priestly Line'
      title: 'Genealogy: The Priestly Line'
      number: 1
      content: '    The sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Amram: Aaron, Moses and Miriam. And the sons of Aaron:
        Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Eleazar became the father of Phinehas, Phinehas became the father
        of Abishua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Abishua became the father of Bukki, and Bukki became the father
        of Uzzi, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Uzzi became the father of Zerahiah, and Zerahiah became the father
        of Meraioth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Meraioth became the father of Amariah, and Amariah became the father
        of Ahitub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and Ahitub became the father of Zadok, and Zadok became the father
        of Ahimaaz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and Ahimaaz became the father of Azariah, and Azariah became the
        father of Johanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and Johanan became the father of Azariah (it was he who was priest
        in the house (temple) which Solomon built in Jerusalem) '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and Azariah became the father of Amariah, and Amariah became the
        father of Ahitub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and Ahitub became the father of Zadok, and Zadok became the father
        of Shallum, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and Shallum became the father of Hilkiah, and Hilkiah became the
        father of Azariah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and Azariah became the father of Seraiah, and Seraiah became the
        father of Jehozadak; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and Jehozadak went into captivity when the Lord sent [the people
        of] Judah and Jerusalem into exile by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  The sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'These are the names of the sons of Gershom: Libni and Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of the
        Levites according to their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Of Gershom: Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, Jeatherai his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Elkanah his son, Ebiasaph his son, Assir his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, and Shaul his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The sons of Elkanah: Amasai and Ahimoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'As for Elkanah, the sons of Elkanah: Zophai his son and Nahath his
        son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elkanah [Samuel\u2019s father] his
        son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Samuel: Joel the firstborn and Abijah the second. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzza his
        son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, Asaiah his son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now these are those whom David appointed over the service of song
        in the house of the Lord after the ark [of the covenant] rested there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "They ministered with singing before the tabernacle of the Tent of
        Meeting, until Solomon had built the Lord\u2019s house (temple) in Jerusalem,
        performing their service in due order. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'These men and their sons served from the Kohathites: Heman the singer,
        the son of Joel, the son of Samuel [the great prophet and judge], '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'the son of Elkanah [III], the son of Jeroham, the son of Eliel, the
        son of Toah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'the son of Zuph, the son of Elkanah [II], the son of Mahath, the
        son of Amasai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'the son of Elkanah [I], the son of Joel, the son of Azariah, the
        son of Zephaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'the son of Tahath, the son of Assir, the son of Ebiasaph, the son
        of Korah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, the son of
        Israel (Jacob). '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Heman\u2019s [tribal] brother Asaph stood at his right hand: Asaph
        the son of Berechiah, the son of Shimea, "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'the son of Michael, the son of Baaseiah, the son of Malchijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'the son of Ethni, the son of Zerah, the son of Adaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'the son of Ethan, the son of Zimmah, the son of Shimei, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'the son of Jahath, the son of Gershom, the son of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Their relatives the sons of Merari stood at the left hand: Ethan
        the son of Kishi, the son of Abdi, the son of Malluch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'the son of Hashabiah, the son of Amaziah, the son of Hilkiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'the son of Amzi, the son of Bani, the son of Shemer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'the son of Mahli, the son of Mushi, the son of Merari, the son of
        Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: Descendants of Aaron'
      title: Descendants of Aaron
      number: 48
      content: 'Their relatives the Levites [who were not descended from Aaron] were
        appointed for all the other kinds of service of the tabernacle of the house
        of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "But [the line of] Aaron and his sons made offerings on the altar
        of burnt offering and on the altar of incense, ministering for all the work
        of the Holy of Holies (Most Holy Place), and [they did so] to make atonement
        for Israel, according to all that Moses, God\u2019s servant, had commanded. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'These are the sons of Aaron: Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son, Abishua
        his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Now these are their settlements according to their camps within their
        borders: to the sons of Aaron of the families of the Kohathites (for theirs
        was the first allocation by lot) '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'to them they gave Hebron in the land of Judah and its surrounding
        pasture land; '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'but the fields of the city and its villages they gave to Caleb the
        son of Jephunneh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'To the sons of Aaron they gave the following cities of refuge: Hebron,
        Libnah with its pasture lands, Jattir, Eshtemoa with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Hilen with its pasture lands, Debir with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Ashan with its pasture lands, and Beth-shemesh with its pasture lands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'and from the tribe of Benjamin: Geba, Alemeth, and Anathoth, with
        their pasture lands. All their cities throughout their families were thirteen
        cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'Then to the rest of the sons of Kohath were given ten cities by lot
        from the family of the tribe [of Ephraim and of Dan and], from the half-tribe,
        the half of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'To the sons of Gershom, according to their families, were given thirteen
        cities from the tribes of Issachar, Asher, Naphtali, and [the other half
        of] Manasseh in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'To the sons of Merari were given twelve cities by lot, according
        to their families, from the tribes of Reuben, Gad, and Zebulun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'So the sons of Israel gave to the Levites these cities with their
        pasture lands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'They gave by lot from the tribes of the sons of Judah, Simeon, and
        Benjamin these cities which are mentioned by name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'Some of the families of the sons of Kohath had cities of their [allotted]
        territory from the tribe of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'They gave to the Levites the following cities of refuge: Shechem
        in the hill country of Ephraim with its pasture lands, Gezer with its pasture
        lands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: 'Jokmeam and Beth-horon with their pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: 'Aijalon and Gath-rimmon, with their pasture lands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: 'and from the half-tribe of Manasseh [these cities], with their pasture
        lands: Aner and Bileam, for the rest of the families of the sons of Kohath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: 'To the sons of Gershom were given from the family of the half-tribe
        of Manasseh: Golan in Bashan and Ashtaroth, with their pasture lands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: 'from the tribe of Issachar: Kedesh and Daberath with their pasture
        lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: 'Ramoth and Anem with their pasture lands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '74: '
      title: 
      number: 74
      content: 'from the tribe of Asher: Mashal and Abdon with their pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '75: '
      title: 
      number: 75
      content: 'Hukok and Rehob with their pasture lands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '76: '
      title: 
      number: 76
      content: 'and from the tribe of Naphtali: Kedesh in Galilee, Hammon, and Kiriathaim
        with their pasture lands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '77: '
      title: 
      number: 77
      content: 'To the rest of the Levites, the sons of Merari were given, from the
        tribe of Zebulun: Rimmono and Tabor, with their pasture lands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '78: '
      title: 
      number: 78
      content: 'and on the other side of the Jordan at Jericho, on the east side
        of the Jordan the Levites were given, from the tribe of Reuben: Bezer in
        the wilderness and Jahzah with their pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '79: '
      title: 
      number: 79
      content: 'Kedemoth and Mephaath with their pasture lands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '80: '
      title: 
      number: 80
      content: 'from the tribe of Gad: Ramoth in Gilead and Mahanaim with their pasture
        lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '81: '
      title: 
      number: 81
      content: Heshbon and Jazer with their pasture lands.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Issachar'
      title: Descendants of Issachar
      number: 1
      content: "  The sons of Issachar were: Tola, Puah, Jashub, and Shimron\u2014four
        in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The sons of Tola: Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Ibsam, and Samuel,
        heads of their fathers\u2019 households. The sons of Tola were courageous
        men in their generations; their number in the days of David was 22,600. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The son of Uzzi: Izrahiah. The sons of Izrahiah: Michael, Obadiah,
        Joel, Isshiah; all five of them were chief men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "With them by their generations according to their fathers\u2019 households
        were 36,000 troops of the army for war, for they had many wives and children. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Descendants of Benjamin'
      title: Descendants of Benjamin
      number: 5
      content: 'Their relatives among all the families of Issachar, courageous men,
        registered by genealogies, were 87,000 in all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The sons of Benjamin were three: Bela, Becher, and Jediael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Bela were five: Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth, and Iri.
        They were heads of the households of their fathers, courageous men. By their
        genealogies they were 22,034. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Becher: Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jeremoth,
        Abijah, Anathoth, and Alemeth, all these were sons of Becher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They were registered by their genealogies according to their generations,
        as heads of their fathers\u2019 households, courageous men, 20,200 in number. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The son of Jediael: Bilhan. The sons of Bilhan: Jeush, Benjamin,
        Ehud, Chenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish, and Ahishahar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "All these were the sons of Jediael, according to the heads of their
        fathers\u2019 households, 17,200 courageous men of valor, fit for military
        service. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Sons of Naphtali'
      title: Sons of Naphtali
      number: 12
      content: 'Shuppim and Huppim were the sons of Ir, and Hushim the son of Aher.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Descendants of Manasseh'
      title: Descendants of Manasseh
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Naphtali: Jahziel, Guni, Jezer, and Shallum, the sons
        of Bilhah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The sons of Manasseh: Asriel, whom his Aramean concubine bore; she
        gave birth to Machir the father of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Machir took as a wife the sister of Huppim and Shuppim; her name
        was Maacah. The name of a second [descendant, the first being Gilead], was
        Zelophehad; and Zelophehad had [only] daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Maacah the wife of Machir gave birth to a son; she named him Peresh.
        The name of his brother was Sheresh; his sons were Ulam and Rakem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The son of Ulam: Bedan. These were the sons of Gilead the son of
        Machir, the son of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'His sister Hammolecheth gave birth to Ishhod and Abiezer and Mahlah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Descendants of Ephraim'
      title: Descendants of Ephraim
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Shemida were: Ahian, Shechem, Likhi, and Aniam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Ephraim: Shuthelah and Bered his son, Tahath [I] his
        son, Eleadah his son, Tahath [II] his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, and Ezer and Elead were killed
        by men who were natives of Gath, because they came down to take their livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Their father Ephraim mourned for many days, and his relatives came
        to comfort him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then he went in to his wife, and she conceived and gave birth to
        a son, and he named him Beriah (on misfortune), because tragedy had come
        on his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Beriah\u2019s daughter was Sheerah, who built both Lower and Upper
        Beth-horon, and also Uzzen-sheerah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Rephah was his son along with Resheph; Resheph\u2019s son was Telah,
        Tahan his son, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ladan his son, Ammihud his son, Elishama his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Non (Nun) his son, and Joshua [Moses\u2019 successor] his son.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Their possessions and settlements were Bethel and its towns, and
        eastward Naaran, and westward Gezer, and Shechem, and as far as Ayyah with
        all their towns, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Descendants of Asher'
      title: Descendants of Asher
      number: 29
      content: 'and along the borders of the sons of Manasseh, Beth-shean, Taanach,
        Megiddo, Dor, with all their towns. In these [places] lived the sons of Joseph
        the son of Israel (Jacob).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, and Beriah; and Serah their
        sister. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sons of Beriah: Heber and Malchiel, who was the father of Birzaith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Heber became the father of Japhlet, Shomer, Hotham, and Shua their
        sister. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Japhlet: Pasach, Bimhal, and Ashvath. These were the
        sons of Japhlet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The sons of Shemer (Shomer) [his brother]: Ahi and Rohgah, Jehubbah,
        and Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of his brother Helem (Hotham): Zophah, Imna, Shelesh, and
        Amal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The sons of Zophah: Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran, and Beera. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The sons of Jether: Jephunneh, Pispa, and Ara. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The sons of Ulla: Arah, Hanniel, and Rizia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "All these were sons (descendants) of Asher, heads of their fathers\u2019
        houses, choice men, courageous men, chiefs of the leaders. Their number,
        enrolled by genealogies for service in war, was 26,000 men."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Genealogy from Benjamin'
      title: Genealogy from Benjamin
      number: 1
      content: '  Benjamin became the father of Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second,
        Aharah the third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Nohah the fourth and Rapha the fifth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Bela had sons: Addar, Gera, Abihud, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Gera, Shephuphan, and Huram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "These are the sons of Ehud: These are the heads of the fathers\u2019
        households of the inhabitants of Geba; they were exiled to Manahath: "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera\u2014he forced them into exile; he became
        the father of Uzza and Ahihud. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Shaharaim became the father of children in the country of Moab after
        he had sent away (divorced) Hushim and Baara his wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'By Hodesh his wife he became the father of Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jeuz, Sachia, and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of fathers\u2019
        households. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'By Hushim he became the father of Abitub and Elpaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Elpaal: Eber, Misham, and Shemed, who built Ono and Lod,
        with its towns; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and Beriah and Shema, who were heads of fathers\u2019 households
        of the inhabitants of Aijalon, who drove out the inhabitants of Gath; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and Ahio, Shashak, and Jeremoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Zebadiah, Arad, Eder, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Michael, Ishpah, and Joha were the sons of Beriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Ishmerai, Izliah, and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Jakim, Zichri, Zabdi, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Ishpan, Eber, Eliel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Abdon, Zichri, Hanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Iphdeiah and Penuel were the sons of Shashak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Jaareshiah, Elijah, and Zichri were the sons of Jeroham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "These [men] were heads of the fathers\u2019 households, according
        to their generations, chief men who lived in Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Now in Gibeon, Jeiel, the father of Gibeon lived, and his wife\u2019s
        name was Maacah; "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'and his firstborn son was Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Gedor, Ahio, and Zecher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Genealogy from King Saul'
      title: Genealogy from King Saul
      number: 32
      content: 'Mikloth became the father of Shimeah. They also lived with their
        relatives in Jerusalem opposite their other relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Ner became the father of Kish, and Kish became the father of [King]
        Saul, and Saul became the father of Jonathan, Malchi-shua, Abinadab and Eshbaal
        (Ish-bosheth). '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The son of Jonathan was Merib-baal (Mephibosheth), and Merib-baal
        became the father of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tarea, and Ahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Ahaz became the father of Jehoaddah, and Jehoaddah became the father
        of Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri; and Zimri became the father of Moza. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Moza became the father of Binea; Raphah was his son, Eleasah his
        son, Azel his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Azel had six sons, and these were their names: Azrikam, Bocheru,
        Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. All these were the sons of Azel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The sons of Eshek his brother: Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the second,
        and Eliphelet the third. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "The sons of Ulam were courageous men, archers, and had many sons
        and grandsons\u2014150 in all. All these were of the sons (descendants) of
        Benjamin."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: People of Jerusalem'
      title: People of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  So all Israel was enrolled by genealogies; and they are written
        in the Book of the Kings of Israel. And Judah was carried away into exile
        to Babylon because of their unfaithfulness [to God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the first [of the returned exiles] who lived [again] in their
        possessions in their cities were Israel, the priests, the Levites, and the
        Nethinim (temple servants). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Some of the sons (people) of Judah, Benjamin, Ephraim, and Manasseh
        lived in Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Uthai the son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son
        of Bani, of the sons of Perez the son of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'From the Shilonites: Asaiah the firstborn and his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'From the sons of Zerah: Jeuel and their relatives, 690 [of them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'From the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son of
        Hodaviah, the son of Hassenuah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ibneiah the son of Jeroham, Elah the son of Uzzi, the son of Michri,
        and Meshullam son of Shephatiah, the son of Reuel, the son of Ibnijah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and their relatives according to their generations, 956. All these
        men were heads of fathers\u2019 households according to their fathers\u2019
        houses.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Of the priests: Jedaiah, Jehoiarib, Jachin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Azariah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok,
        the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the chief officer of the house of
        God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah;
        Maasai the son of Adiel, the son of Jahzerah, the son of Meshullam, the son
        of Meshillemith, the son of Immer; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and their relatives, heads of their fathers\u2019 households, 1,760\u2014very
        able men for the work of the service of the house of God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam,
        the son of Hashabiah, of the sons of Merari; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and Bakbakkar, Heresh, Galal, and Mattaniah son of Mica, the son
        of Zichri, the son of Asaph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun,
        and Berechiah the son of Asa, the son of Elkanah, who lived in the villages
        of the Netophathites [near Jerusalem].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The gatekeepers were: Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, Ahiman, and their relatives
        (Shallum the chief '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "who until now was assigned to the king\u2019s gate on the east side)
        they were the gatekeepers for the camp of the Levites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Shallum the son of Kore, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, and
        his relatives of his father\u2019s house, the Korahites, were in charge of
        the work of the service, doorkeepers of the Tent; and their fathers had been
        in charge of the camp of the Lord, keepers of the entrance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Phinehas the son of Eleazar was ruler over them in times past, and
        the Lord was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Zechariah son of Meshelemiah was gatekeeper at the entrance of the
        Tent of Meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'All those chosen to be gatekeepers at the thresholds were 212. They
        were enrolled by their genealogies in their villages [around Jerusalem],
        these men [whose grandfathers] David and Samuel the seer had appointed to
        their official duty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So they and their sons were in charge of the gates of the house of
        the Lord, that is, the house of the tabernacle, as guards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The gatekeepers were stationed on the four sides \u2014on the east,
        west, north, and south. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their relatives in their villages were to come in every seven days
        from time to time to be with them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'for these Levites, the four chief gatekeepers, had an official duty,
        and were in charge of the chambers and treasuries of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They spent the night around the house of God, for the [night] watch
        was theirs, and they were in charge of opening the house morning after morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now some of them were in charge of the serving utensils, being required
        to count them when they brought them in or took them out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Some of them also were appointed over the furniture and over all
        the [sacred] utensils of the sanctuary, as well as over the fine flour and
        the wine and the [olive] oil and the frankincense and the spices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Other sons of the priests prepared the mixture of spices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Mattithiah, one of the Levites, the firstborn of Shallum the Korahite,
        was responsible for the things baked in pans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Some of their Kohathite relatives were in charge of the showbread
        to prepare it every Sabbath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Now these are the singers, heads of the fathers\u2019 households
        of the Levites, living in the temple chambers, free from other service because
        they were on duty day and night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Ancestry and Descendants of Saul'
      title: Ancestry and Descendants of Saul
      number: 34
      content: "These were heads of fathers\u2019 households of the Levites according
        to their generations, chief men, who lived in Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jeiel the father of Gibeon lived in Gibeon, and his wife\u2019s name
        was Maacah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and his firstborn son was Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah, and Mikloth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Mikloth became the father of Shimeam. They also lived with their
        relatives in Jerusalem, opposite their other relatives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Ner became the father of Kish, and Kish became the father of [King]
        Saul, and Saul became the father of Jonathan, Malchi-shua, Abinadab, and
        Esh-baal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The son of Jonathan was Merib-baal (Mephibosheth); Merib-baal became
        the father of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tahrea [and Ahaz]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Ahaz became the father of Jarah, and Jarah became the father of Alemeth,
        Azmaveth, and Zimri; and Zimri became the father of Moza, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Moza became the father of Binea and Rephaiah his son, Eleasah his
        son, Azel his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Azel had six sons, and these are their names: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael,
        Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. These were the sons of Azel.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Defeat and Death of Saul and His Sons'
      title: Defeat and Death of Saul and His Sons
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Philistines fought against Israel; and the men of Israel
        fled from them and fell slain on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Philistines followed closely after Saul and his sons and overtook
        them, and the Philistines killed Jonathan, Abinadab, and Malchi-shua, the
        sons of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The battle became heavy against Saul, and the archers found him;
        and he was [mortally] wounded by the archers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Saul said to his armor bearer, \u201CDraw your sword and run
        me through with it, otherwise these uncircumcised [Philistines] will come
        and abuse and humiliate me.\u201D But his armor bearer would not, for he
        was terrified. So Saul took his own sword and fell on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When his armor bearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell on his
        sword and died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Saul died with his three sons and all those of his house died
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When all the men of Israel who were in the valley saw that the army
        had fled, and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned their cities
        and fled; and the Philistines came and lived in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It came about the next day, when the Philistines came to strip (plunder)
        the slain, that they found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So they stripped Saul and took his head and his armor and sent messengers
        around the land of the Philistines to bring the good news to their idols
        and to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Jabesh-gilead\u2019s Tribute to Saul"
      title: "Jabesh-gilead\u2019s Tribute to Saul"
      number: 10
      content: "They put Saul\u2019s armor in the house of their gods and nailed
        up his head in the house (temple) of Dagon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When all Jabesh-gilead heard about everything that the Philistines
        had done to Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'all the brave men arose, took away the body of Saul and the bodies
        of his sons and brought them to Jabesh, and they buried their bones under
        the oak in Jabesh; then they fasted seven days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Saul died for his trespass which he committed against the Lord,
        for his failure to keep the word of the Lord; and also because he consulted
        a medium [regarding a spirit of the dead], to inquire of her, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: and did not inquire of the Lord [instead]. Therefore the Lord killed
        him and turned the kingdom over to David the son of Jesse.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Made King over All Israel'
      title: David Made King over All Israel
      number: 1
      content: "    Then all Israel gathered to David at Hebron, saying, \u201CBehold,
        we are your bone and your flesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In times past, even when Saul was king, it was you who led out and
        brought in Israel; and the Lord your God said to you, \u2018You shall shepherd
        My people Israel, and you shall be prince and leader over My people Israel.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Jerusalem, Capital City'
      title: Jerusalem, Capital City
      number: 3
      content: 'So all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and David
        made a covenant (solemn agreement) with them there before the Lord; and they
        anointed him king over Israel, in accordance with the word of the Lord through
        Samuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then David and all Israel went to Jerusalem (that is Jebus); and
        the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, were there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Jebusites said to David, \u201CYou shall not come in here.\u201D
        But David captured the stronghold of Zion (that is, the City of David). "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now David said, \u201CWhoever strikes down a Jebusite first shall
        be chief and commander.\u201D Joab the son of Zeruiah [David\u2019s half
        sister] went up first, and so he was made chief. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then David lived in the stronghold; so it was called the City of
        David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He built the city around it, from the Millo (fortification) to the
        surrounding area; and Joab repaired the rest of the [old Jebusite] city. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      title: "David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      number: 9
      content: 'David became greater and greater, for the Lord of hosts was with
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now these are the chiefs of David\u2019s mighty men, who strongly
        supported him in his kingdom, together with all Israel, to make him king,
        in accordance with the word of the Lord concerning Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "This is the list of David\u2019s mighty men: Jashobeam, the son of
        a Hachmonite, the chief of the thirty [heroes]. He lifted up his spear against
        three hundred whom he killed at one time.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Next to him [in rank] was Eleazar the son of Dodo the Ahohite, who
        was one of the three mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He was with David at Pasdammim [where David had killed Goliath] and
        there the Philistines were gathered together for battle, and there was a
        plot of ground full of barley; and the people [of Israel] fled before the
        Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But they took their stand in the midst of that plot and defended
        it, and killed the Philistines; and the Lord rescued them by a great victory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Three of the thirty chief men went down to the rock to David, into
        the cave of Adullam, while the army of the Philistines was camped in the
        Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David was then in the stronghold, while the garrison of the Philistines
        was in Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "David had a craving and said, \u201COh that someone would give me
        a drink of water from the well of Bethlehem, which is next to the gate!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the three [mighty men] broke through the camp of the Philistines
        and drew water out of the well of Bethlehem which was next to the gate, and
        brought it to David. But David would not drink it; he poured it out to the
        Lord [as an offering]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and he said, \u201CFar be it from me before my God that I would do
        this thing! Shall I drink the blood of these men who have put their lives
        in jeopardy? For they brought it at the risk of their lives.\u201D So he
        would not drink it. These things the three mighty men did.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Abishai the brother of Joab was chief of the [other] three, and he
        lifted up his spear against three hundred and killed them, and he had a name
        as well as the three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Of the three in the second [rank] he was the most honored and became
        their captain; however, he did not attain to the first three [Jashobeam,
        Eleazar, and Shammah].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a courageous man of Kabzeel
        who had done great things, killed the two sons of Ariel of Moab. Also he
        went down and killed a lion in a pit on a snowy day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He killed an Egyptian also, a man of great stature, five cubits tall.
        In the Egyptian\u2019s hand was a spear like a weaver\u2019s beam, and Benaiah
        went down to him with [only] a staff (rod) and grabbed the spear from the
        Egyptian\u2019s hand and killed him with his own spear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did these things, and had a name as well
        as the three mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He was honored among the thirty, but he did not attain to [the rank
        of] the [first] three. David appointed him over his bodyguard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the mighty men of the armies were: Asahel the brother of Joab,
        Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Shammoth the Harorite, Helez the Pelonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ira the son of Ikkesh of Tekoa, Abiezer of Anathoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Sibbecai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Maharai the Netophathite, Heled the son of Baanah the Netophathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Ithai the son of Ribai of Gibeah of the Benjamites, Benaiah the Pirathonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Hurai of the brooks of Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Azmaveth the Baharumite, Eliahba the Shaalbonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'the sons of Hashem the Gizonite, Jonathan the son of Shagee the Hararite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Ahiam the son of Sacar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Ur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Hepher the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Hezro the Carmelite, Naarai the son of Ezbai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Joel the brother of Nathan, Mibhar the son of Hagri, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Berothite, the armor bearer of Joab
        the son of Zeruiah [David\u2019s half sister], "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Uriah the Hittite [Bathsheba\u2019s husband], Zabad the son of Ahlai, "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Adina the son of Shiza the Reubenite, a chief of the Reubenites,
        and thirty [heroes] with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Hanan the son of Maacah, and Joshaphat the Mithnite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Uzzia the Ashterathite, Shama and Jeiel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jediael the son of Shimri, and his brother Joha, the Tizite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Eliel the Mahavite, Jeribai and Joshaviah the sons of Elnaam, Ithmah
        the Moabite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Eliel and Obed and Jaasiel the Mezobaite.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Supporters in Ziklag"
      title: "David\u2019s Supporters in Ziklag"
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the ones who came to David at Ziklag, while he still
        concealed himself from Saul the son of Kish; they were among the courageous
        men who helped him in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "They were armed with bows, and could use the right hand or the left
        to sling stones and shoot arrows from the bow; they were Saul\u2019s relatives
        from [the tribe of] Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The chief was Ahiezer and then Joash, the sons of Shemaah of Gibeah;
        Jeziel and Pelet the sons of Azmaveth; Beracah, and Jehu of Anathoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ishmaiah of Gibeon, a mighty man among the thirty, and [a leader]
        over them; Jeremiah, Jahaziel, Johanan, Jozabad of Gederah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Eluzai, Jerimoth, Bealiah, Shemariah, Shephatiah the Haruphite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Elkanah, Isshiah, Azarel, Joezer, and Jashobeam, the Korahites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and Joelah and Zebadiah the sons of Jeroham of Gedor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Courageous men from the Gadites came over to David in the stronghold
        in the wilderness, men trained for war, who could handle shield and spear,
        whose faces were like the faces of lions, and who were swift as gazelles
        on the mountains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ezer was the first, Obadiah the second, Eliab the third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Mishmannah the fourth, Jeremiah the fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Attai the sixth, Eliel the seventh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Johanan the eighth, Elzabad the ninth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jeremiah the tenth, Machbannai the eleventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These from the sons (descendants) of Gad were captains of the army;
        he who was least was equal to a hundred, and the greatest was equal to a
        thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These are the men who crossed over the Jordan in the first month
        when it had overflowed all its banks and they put to flight all those in
        the valleys, east and west.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then some of the men of Benjamin and Judah came to the stronghold
        to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "David went out to meet them and said to them, \u201CIf you have come
        peacefully to me to help me, my heart shall be united with you; but if you
        have come to betray me to my adversaries, since there is no violence or wrong
        in my hands, may the God of our fathers look on [what you are doing] and
        punish [you].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the [Holy] Spirit came on Amasai, who was chief of the thirty,
        and he said,\u201CWe are yours, O David,And with you, O son of Jesse!Peace,
        peace be to you,And peace be to him who helps you;For your God helps you.\u201DThen
        David accepted and received them and made them officers of his troops.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Some [of the men] of Manasseh also defected to David when he came
        with the Philistines to go to battle against Saul. But David\u2019s men did
        not [actually] assist the Philistines, for the lords (governors) of the Philistines
        after consultation sent him away, saying, \u201CAt the cost of our heads
        he may defect to his master Saul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As David went to Ziklag, these men defected to him from Manasseh:
        Adnah, Jozabad, Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu, and Zillethai, captains
        of thousands who belonged to Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They helped David against the band of raiders, for they were all
        courageous men, and [all seven] became commanders in his army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Supporters Gathered at Hebron'
      title: Supporters Gathered at Hebron
      number: 22
      content: 'For day by day men kept coming to David to help him, until there
        was a great army, like the army of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These are the numbers of the [armed] units equipped for war who came
        to David at Hebron to turn [over] the kingdom of Saul to him, in accordance
        with the word of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Those of the tribe of Judah who carried shield and spear were 6,800,
        armed for war; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'of the tribe of Simeon, brave warriors, 7,100; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'of the tribe of Levi, 4,600. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Jehoiada was the leader of [the house of] Aaron, and with him were
        3,700, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and Zadok, a courageous young man, and twenty-two captains from his
        father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Of the tribe of Benjamin, the relatives of [King] Saul, 3,000; for
        until now the majority of them had kept their allegiance to the house of
        Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Of the tribe of Ephraim, 20,800, courageous men, famous in their
        fathers\u2019 houses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Of the half-tribe of Manasseh, 18,000, who were designated by name
        to come and make David king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Of the tribe of Issachar, men who understood the times, with knowledge
        of what Israel should do, two hundred chiefs; and all their relatives were
        at their command; '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'of the tribe of Zebulun, there were 50,000 in military service who
        could draw up in battle formation with all kinds of weapons of war and helped
        David, men with an undivided heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Of the tribe of Naphtali, there were 1,000 captains, and with them
        37,000 [of the rank and file armed] with shield and spear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Of the tribe of Dan, 28,600 men who could draw up in battle formation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Of the tribe of Asher, 40,000 men in military service, able to draw
        up in battle formation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'From the other side [east] of the Jordan River, of [the tribes of]
        Reuben and Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh, 120,000 men, armed with all
        kinds of weapons of war for the battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'All these, being men of war arrayed in battle formation, came to
        Hebron with a perfect (committed) heart to make David king over all Israel;
        and all the rest of Israel were also of one mind to make David king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'They were there with David for three days, eating and drinking, for
        their relatives had prepared for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: Also those who were [living] near them [from] as far as [the tribes
        of] Issachar, Zebulun, and Naphtali, brought food on donkeys, camels, mules,
        and oxen, abundant supplies of flour, cakes of figs and raisins, wine, [olive]
        oil, oxen, and sheep, for there was joy in Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peril in Transporting the Ark'
      title: Peril in Transporting the Ark
      number: 1
      content: '  David consulted with the captains of the thousands and the hundreds,
        even with every leader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David said to all the assembly of Israel, \u201CIf it seems good
        to you, and if it is from the Lord our God, let us send word everywhere to
        our fellow countrymen who remain in all the land of Israel, and to the priests
        and Levites who are with them in their cities with pasture lands, so that
        they may meet with us; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and let us bring back the ark of our God to us, for we did not seek
        it during the days of Saul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then all the assembly agreed to do so, for the thing was right in
        the eyes of all the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So David gathered all Israel together, from the Shihor [watercourse]
        of Egypt, to the entrance of Hamath [in the north], to bring the ark of God
        from Kiriath-jearim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'David and all Israel went up to Baalah, that is, to Kiriath-jearim,
        which belongs to Judah, to bring up from there the ark of God the Lord who
        sits enthroned above the cherubim, the ark which is called by His name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They carried the ark of God on a new cart and brought it out of the
        house of Abinadab, and Uzza and Ahio [his brother] drove the cart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'David and all Israel celebrated [joyfully] before God with all their
        might, with songs, lyres, harps, tambourines, cymbals, and trumpets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When they came to the threshing floor of Chidon, Uzza put out his
        hand to hold and steady the ark, for the oxen [that were drawing the cart]
        nearly overturned it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The anger of the Lord burned against Uzza, and He struck him down
        because he touched the ark; and there he died before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "David became angry because of the Lord\u2019s outburst against Uzza;
        so that place is called Perez-uzza to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "David was afraid of God that day, and he said, \u201CHow can I bring
        the ark of God home with me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So David did not bring the ark with him to the City of David, but
        took it aside to the house of Obed-edom the Gittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So the ark of God remained with the family of Obed-edom in his house
        three months; and the Lord  blessed the house of Obed-edom and all that he
        had.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Family Enlarged"
      title: "David\u2019s Family Enlarged"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David with cedar timbers,
        masons and carpenters, to build a house (palace) for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And David understood that the Lord had established and confirmed
        him as king over Israel, for his kingdom was highly exalted for the sake
        of His people Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then David took more wives at Jerusalem, and he became the father
        of more sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now these are the names of the children born [to him] in Jerusalem:
        Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Philistines Defeated'
      title: Philistines Defeated
      number: 7
      content: 'Elishama, Beeliada, and Eliphelet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over
        all Israel, they all went up in search of David; and he heard about it and
        went out against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the Philistines had come and made a raid in the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So David inquired of God, \u201CShall I go up against the Philistines?
        And will You hand them over to me?\u201D Then the Lord said to him, \u201CGo
        up, and I will hand them over to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Israel came up to Baal-perazim, and David defeated the Philistines
        there. Then David said, \u201CGod has broken through my enemies by my hand,
        like the breakthrough of waters.\u201D Therefore they named that place Baal-perazim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Philistines abandoned their gods (idols) there; so David gave
        a command and they were burned in a fire [as the Law of Moses required].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The Philistines again made a raid in the valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So David inquired again of God, and God said to him, \u201CDo not
        go up after them; circle around behind them and come at them in front of
        the balsam trees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "It shall be when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the
        balsam trees, then you shall go out to battle, for God has gone out before
        you to strike the Philistine army.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So David did just as God had commanded him, and they struck down
        the army of the Philistines from Gibeon as far as Gezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then David\u2019s fame spread into all the lands; and the Lord caused
        all nations to fear him."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Plans to Move the Ark to Jerusalem'
      title: Plans to Move the Ark to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '    David built houses for himself in the City of David; and he prepared
        a place for the ark of God and pitched a tent for it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then David said, \u201CNo one is to carry the ark of God except the
        Levites; for the Lord chose them to carry the ark of God and to minister
        to Him forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David assembled all Israel at Jerusalem to bring up the ark of
        the Lord to the place which he had prepared for it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David gathered together the sons of Aaron and the Levites: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'of the sons of Kohath, Uriel the chief, with 120 of his relatives; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'of the sons of Merari, Asaiah the chief, with 220 of his relatives; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'of the sons of Gershom, Joel the chief, with 130 of his relatives; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'of the sons of Elizaphan, Shemaiah the chief, with 200 of his relatives; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'of the sons of Hebron, Eliel the chief, with 80 of his relatives; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'of the sons of Uzziel, Amminadab the chief, with 112 of his relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then David called for Zadok and Abiathar the priests, and for the
        Levites\u2014Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel, and Amminadab, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and he said to them, \u201CYou are the heads of the fathers\u2019
        households of the Levites; consecrate yourselves, both you and your relatives,
        so that you may bring up the ark of the Lord God of Israel, to the place
        that I have prepared for it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Because you did not [carry it as God directed] the first time, the
        Lord our God made an [angry] outburst against us, for we did not seek Him
        in accordance with the ordinance.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the priests and the Levites consecrated (dedicated) themselves
        to bring up the ark of the Lord God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Levites carried the ark of God on their shoulders with the poles,
        as Moses commanded in accordance with the word of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then David told the chiefs of the Levites to appoint their relatives
        as the singers, with instruments of music\u2014harps, lyres, and cymbals\u2014to
        play loudly and to raise sounds of joy [with their voices]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the Levites appointed Heman the son of Joel, and from his relatives,
        Asaph the son of Berechiah; and from the sons of Merari their relatives,
        Ethan the son of Kushaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and with them their relatives of the second rank: Zechariah, Ben,
        Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattithiah,
        Eliphelehu, and Mikneiah, Obed-edom, and Jeiel, the gatekeepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So the singers, Heman, Asaph, and Ethan were appointed to sound aloud
        the bronze cymbals; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and Zechariah, Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah,
        and Benaiah [were to play] with harps tuned to Alamoth [that is, a high pitch]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-edom, Jeiel, and Azaziah
        were to lead with lyres set to Sheminith [that is, the eighth string, a low
        pitch]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Chenaniah, leader of the Levites, was in charge of the singing; he
        gave instruction in singing because he was skilled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Berechiah and Elkanah were gatekeepers for the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Shebaniah, Joshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zechariah, Benaiah, and Eliezer
        the priests blew the trumpets before the ark of God. Obed-edom and Jehiah
        (Jeiel) were also gatekeepers for the ark.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So David, with the elders of Israel and the captains over thousands,
        went to bring up the ark of the covenant of the Lord from the house of Obed-edom
        with joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Because God was helping the Levites who carried the ark of the covenant
        of the Lord [to do it carefully and safely], they sacrificed seven bulls
        and seven rams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'David was clothed with a robe of fine linen, as were all the Levites
        who carried the ark, and the singers and Chenaniah, director of the music
        of the singers. David also wore an ephod (a priestly upper garment) of linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Thus all Israel brought up the ark of the covenant of the Lord with
        shouting, and with the sound of the horn, with trumpets, with loud-sounding
        cymbals, with harps and lyres.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "It happened that as the ark of the covenant of the Lord came to the
        City of David, Michal [David\u2019s wife] the daughter of Saul, looking down
        through a window, saw King David leaping and dancing [in celebration]; and
        she despised him in her heart."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Tent for the Ark'
      title: A Tent for the Ark
      number: 1
      content: '  So they brought the ark of God and set it inside the tent which
        David had pitched for it, and they offered burnt offerings and peace offerings
        before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When David had finished offering the burnt offerings and the peace
        offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He distributed to everyone in Israel, both man and woman, to everyone
        a loaf of bread, a portion of meat, and a raisin cake.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He appointed some of the Levites to minister before the ark of the
        Lord and to profess [God\u2019s name] and to thank and praise the Lord, the
        God of Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Asaph the chief, and second to him Zechariah, then Jeiel (Jaaziel),
        Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Benaiah, Obed-edom, and Jeiel with
        musical instruments, harps and lyres; also Asaph played loud-sounding cymbals; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests blew trumpets continually before
        the ark of the covenant of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Psalm of Thanksgiving'
      title: Psalm of Thanksgiving
      number: 7
      content: 'Then on that day David first entrusted to Asaph and his relatives
        to give thanks to the Lord [as their chief task].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O give thanks to the Lord, call on His name;Make His deeds known
        among the peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Sing to Him, sing praises to Him;Speak of all His wonders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Glory in His holy name;Let the hearts of those who seek the Lord
        rejoice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Seek the Lord and His strength;Seek His face continually [longing
        to be in His presence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Remember [with gratitude] His marvelous deeds which He has done,His
        miracles and the judgments from His mouth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O seed of Israel His servant,  Children of Jacob, His chosen ones!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He is the Lord our God;His judgments are in all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Be mindful of His covenant forever,The promise which He commanded
        and established to a thousand generations,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  The covenant which He made with Abraham,And His oath (sworn promise)
        to Isaac.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He confirmed it as a statute to Jacob,And to Israel as an everlasting
        covenant,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Saying, \u201CTo you I will give the land of Canaan,As the portion
        of your possession and inheritance.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When you were few in number,Even a very few, and strangers in it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When they wandered from nation to nation,And from one kingdom to
        another people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He allowed no man to oppress or exploit them,And, He reproved and
        punished kings for their sakes, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CDo not touch My anointed ones,And do My prophets no harm.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Sing to the Lord, all the earth;Proclaim the good news of His salvation
        from day to day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Declare His glory among the nations,His marvelous works among all
        peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For great is the Lord, and greatly to be praised;He is also to be
        feared [with awe-filled reverence] above all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For all the gods of the peoples are [lifeless] idols,But the Lord
        made the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Splendor and majesty are [found] in His presence;Strength and joy
        are [found] in His place (sanctuary).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ascribe to the Lord, O families of the peoples,Ascribe to the Lord
        glory and honor and strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Ascribe to the Lord the glory and honor due His name;Bring an offering
        [of thanksgiving], and come before Him;Worship the Lord in the splendor of
        holiness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Tremble [reverently] before Him, all the earth;The world is firmly
        established, it will not be moved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Let the heavens be glad, and let the earth rejoice;And let them say
        among the nations, \u201CThe Lord reigns.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Let the sea roar, and all the things that fill it;Let the field rejoice,
        and all that is in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then the trees of the forest will sing for joy before the Lord;For
        He comes to judge and govern the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'O give thanks to the Lord, for He is good;For His lovingkindness
        endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then say, \u201CSave us, O God of our salvation;Gather us together
        and rescue us from the nations,That we may give thanks to Your holy name,And
        glory in Your praise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Worship before the Ark'
      title: Worship before the Ark
      number: 36
      content: "Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,Forever and ever.And all the
        people said, \u201CAmen,\u201D and praised the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So David left Asaph and his relatives there before the ark of the
        covenant of the Lord to minister before the ark continually, as each day\u2019s
        work required; "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and Obed-edom with his sixty-eight relatives; also Obed-edom the
        son of Jeduthun, and Hosah, were to be gatekeepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'David left Zadok the priest and his relatives the priests before
        the dwelling place (tabernacle) of the Lord in the high place which was at
        Gibeon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'to offer burnt offerings to the Lord on the altar of burnt offering
        continually, morning and evening, in accordance with all that is written
        in the Law of the Lord, which He commanded Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'With them were Heman and Jeduthun, and the rest who were chosen and
        designated by name, to give thanks to the Lord, for His lovingkindness endures
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'With them were Heman and Jeduthun with trumpets and cymbals for those
        who were to sound aloud, and instruments for [accompanying] the songs of
        God. And the sons of Jeduthun were to be at the gate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Then all the people departed, each to his house, and David returned
        [home] to bless his household.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Covenant with David"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with David"
      number: 1
      content: "  As David sat in his house (palace), he said to Nathan the prophet,
        \u201CBehold, I live in a house of cedars, while the ark of the covenant
        of the Lord is under tent curtains.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Nathan said to David, \u201CDo all that is in your heart, for
        God is with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But it came about that same night that the word of God came to Nathan,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGo and tell David My servant, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CYou
        shall not build a house for Me to dwell in; "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'for I have not dwelt in a house since the day that I brought Israel
        up [from Egypt] until this day, but I have gone from tent to tent and from
        one dwelling place to another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Wherever I have walked with all Israel, did I say a word to any of
        the judges of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd My people, saying, \u2018Why
        have you not built for Me a house of cedar?\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now, therefore, this is what you shall say to My servant David: \u2018Thus
        says the Lord of hosts, \u201CI took you from the pasture, from following
        the sheep, to be leader over My people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I have been with you wherever you have gone, and I have cut off all
        your enemies from before you; and I will make your name like the name of
        the great ones of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will appoint a place for My people Israel, and will plant them,
        so that they may live in their own place and not be moved again [nor tremble
        with fear]; and the wicked will not waste (persecute) them anymore, as formerly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "since the time that I commanded judges to be over My people Israel.
        And I will humble and subdue all your enemies.\u201CFurthermore, I tell you
        that the Lord will build you a house (a blessed posterity). "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it shall come to pass that when your days are completed and you
        must go to be with your fathers [in death], I will raise up one of your descendants
        after you, one of your own sons; and I will establish his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He shall build Me a house, and I will establish his throne forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will be his father and he shall be My son; and I will not take
        My steadfast love and mercy away from him, as I took it from him (King Saul)
        who was before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But I will settle him in My house and in My kingdom forever, and
        his throne shall be established forevermore.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: David\u2019s Prayer in Response"
      title: "David\u2019s Prayer in Response"
      number: 15
      content: 'According to all these words and according to all this vision, so
        Nathan spoke to David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then David the king went in and sat before the Lord and said, \u201CWho
        am I, O Lord God, and what is my house and family that You have brought me
        this far? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "This was a small thing in Your eyes, O God; but You have spoken of
        Your servant\u2019s house for a great while to come, and have regarded me
        according to the standard and estate of a man of high degree (prominence),
        O Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'What more can David say to You for the honor granted to Your servant?
        For You know Your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "O Lord, for Your servant\u2019s sake, and in accordance with Your
        own heart, You have accomplished all this greatness, to make known all these
        great things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'O Lord, there is no one like You, nor is there any God except You,
        according to all that we have heard with our ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And what one nation on the earth is like Your people Israel, whom
        God went to redeem for Himself as a people, to make a name for Yourself by
        great and awesome and terrible things, by driving out nations from before
        Your people, whom You redeemed out of Egypt? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You made Your people Israel Your own people forever, and You, Lord,
        became their God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CTherefore now, O Lord, let the word which You have spoken concerning
        Your servant and his house endure forever, and do as You have said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Let Your name [and the character that it denotes] endure and be magnified
        forever, saying, \u2018The Lord of hosts is the God of Israel, yes, a God
        to Israel; and the house of Your servant David is established before You.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For You, O my God, have revealed to Your servant that You will build
        for him a house (descendants); therefore Your servant has found courage to
        pray before You. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And now, O Lord, You are God, and you have spoken and promised this
        good thing to Your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore may it please You to bless the house (descendants) of Your
        servant, that it may continue before You forever; for what You bless, O Lord,
        is blessed forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Kingdom Strengthened"
      title: "David\u2019s Kingdom Strengthened"
      number: 1
      content: '  After this it came about that David defeated and subdued the Philistines,
        and he took Gath and its villages out of the hand of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He defeated Moab, and the Moabites became David\u2019s servants and
        brought tribute (gifts).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David also defeated Hadadezer king of Zobah as far as Hamath, as
        he went to establish his dominion to the Euphrates River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David took from him 1,000 chariots, 7,000 horsemen, and 20,000 foot
        soldiers (infantrymen). David also hamstrung [nearly] all the chariot horses
        [to make them lame and useless], but left enough of them for 100 chariots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the Arameans (Syrians) of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king
        of Zobah, David killed 22,000 of the Arameans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David put military outposts among the Arameans in Damascus;
        and the Arameans became David\u2019s servants and brought tribute. Thus the
        Lord helped David wherever he went. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'David took the shields of gold which were carried by the servants
        of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Likewise from Tibhath and from Cun, cities of Hadadezer, David brought
        a very large amount of bronze, with which Solomon later made the bronze Sea
        (large basin), the pillars, and the utensils of bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Tou king of Hamath heard how David had defeated all the army
        of Hadadezer king of Zobah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'he sent Hadoram his son to King David to greet him and to bless (congratulate)
        him, because he had fought against Hadadezer and had defeated him; for Hadadezer
        had been at war with Tou. And Hadoram brought all kinds of articles of gold
        and silver and bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'King David also dedicated these to the Lord [setting them apart for
        sacred use], with the silver and the gold which he brought from all the nations:
        from Edom, Moab, the Ammonites, the Philistines, and from Amalek.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Also Abishai the son of Zeruiah [David\u2019s half sister] defeated
        18,000 Edomites in the Valley of Salt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He put military outposts in Edom, and all the Edomites became David\u2019s
        servants. Thus the Lord helped David wherever he went.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So David reigned over all Israel and administered justice and righteousness
        for all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Joab the son of Zeruiah was in command of the army, and Jehoshaphat
        the son of Ahilud was the recorder; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Zadok the son of Ahitub and Abimelech the son of Abiathar were the
        priests, and Shavsha was secretary (state scribe); '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was in charge of the Cherethites
        and the Pelethites [David\u2019s bodyguards], and the sons of David were
        chiefs at the king\u2019s side."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Messengers Abused"
      title: "David\u2019s Messengers Abused"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it came about after this, that Nahash king of the Ammonites
        died, and his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David said, \u201CI will be kind (gracious) to Hanun son of Nahash,
        because his father was kind to me.\u201D So David sent messengers to comfort
        him concerning [the death of] his father. And the servants of David came
        to the land of the Ammonites to comfort Hanun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the leaders of the Ammonites said to Hanun, \u201CDo you think
        that David has sent people to console and comfort you because he honors your
        father? Have his servants not come to you to search and to overthrow and
        to spy out the land?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore Hanun took David\u2019s servants, shaved them [cutting
        off half their beards], and cut off their garments in the middle as far as
        their buttocks, and sent them away [in humiliation]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When David was told how the men were treated, he sent messengers
        to meet them, for they were very humiliated and ashamed [to return]. So the
        king said, \u201CStay in Jericho until your beards grow [back], and then
        return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the Ammonites saw that they had made themselves hateful to David,
        Hanun and his people sent 1,000 talents of silver to hire for themselves
        chariots and horsemen from Mesopotamia, Aram-maacah, and Zobah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they hired for themselves 32,000 chariots and the king of Maacah
        and his troops, who came and camped before Medeba. And the Ammonites gathered
        together from their cities and came to battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When David heard about it, he sent Joab and all the army of courageous
        men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Ammon and Aram Defeated'
      title: Ammon and Aram Defeated
      number: 9
      content: 'The Ammonites came out and lined up in battle formation at the entrance
        of the city [Medeba], while the kings who had come were by themselves in
        the open country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now when Joab saw that the battle was set against him in the front
        and in the rear, he chose warriors from all the choice men of Israel and
        put them in formation against the Arameans (Syrians). '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The rest of the soldiers he placed in the hand of Abishai his brother,
        and they lined up against the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He said, \u201CIf the Arameans are too strong for me, then you shall
        help me; but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, I will help you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Be strong and let us show ourselves courageous for the sake of our
        people and for the cities of our God; and may the Lord do what is good in
        His sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Joab and the people who were with him approached the Arameans
        for battle, and they fled before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When the Ammonites saw that the Arameans fled, they also fled before
        Abishai, Joab\u2019s brother, and entered the city [Medeba]. Then Joab came
        to Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When the Arameans (Syrians) saw that they had been defeated by Israel,
        they sent messengers and brought out the Arameans who were beyond the [Euphrates]
        River, with Shophach the commander of the army of Hadadezer leading them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When this was told to David, he gathered all Israel and crossed the
        Jordan, and came upon them and drew up in formation against them. So when
        David drew up in battle array against the Arameans, they fought against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the Arameans fled before Israel, and David killed of the Arameans
        7,000 charioteers and 40,000 foot soldiers, and put to death Shophach the
        commander of the army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: When the servants of Hadadezer saw that they had been defeated by
        Israel, they made peace with David and became subject to and served him.
        And the Arameans (Syrians) were not willing to help the Ammonites anymore.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: War with Philistine Giants'
      title: War with Philistine Giants
      number: 1
      content: '  Then it happened at the end of the year, at the time when kings
        go out to battle, Joab led out the army and ravaged and devastated the land
        of the Ammonites, and came and besieged Rabbah. But David stayed at Jerusalem
        [with Bathsheba]. Joab struck Rabbah and overthrew it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David took the crown of their king from his head and found that it
        weighed a talent of gold and that there was a precious stone in it; so it
        was set on David\u2019s head. He also brought a very great amount of spoil
        (plunder) out of the city [of Rabbah]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He brought out the people who were in it, and put them [to work]
        with saws, iron picks, and axes. David dealt in this way with all the Ammonite
        cities. Then David and all the people returned to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now it came about after this that war broke out at Gezer with the
        Philistines; then Sibbecai the Hushathite killed Sippai, one of the descendants
        of the giants, and they were subdued. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "There was war again with the Philistines, and Elhanan the son of
        Jair killed Lahmi the brother of Goliath the Gittite, the shaft of whose
        spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Again there was war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature
        who had twenty-four fingers and toes, six fingers on each hand and six toes
        on each foot; and he also was descended from the giants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When he taunted Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimea, David\u2019s
        brother, killed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: These were descended from the giants in Gath, and they fell by the
        hand of David and by the hand of his servants.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Census Brings Pestilence'
      title: Census Brings Pestilence
      number: 1
      content: '  Satan [the adversary] stood up against Israel and incited David
        to count [the population of] Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So David said to Joab and the leaders of the people, \u201CGo, count
        Israel from Beersheba to Dan, and bring me their total, so that I may know
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Joab said, \u201CMay the Lord add to His people a hundred times as
        many as they are! But, my lord the king, are they not all my lord\u2019s
        servants? Why then does my lord require this? Why will he bring guilt on
        Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the king\u2019s word prevailed over Joab. So Joab left and went
        throughout all Israel and came to Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Joab gave the total of the census of the people to David. And
        all Israel were 1,100,000 men who drew the sword; and in Judah 470,000 men
        who drew the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he did not count Levi and Benjamin among them, because the king\u2019s
        order was detestable to Joab.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now God was displeased with this act [of arrogance and pride], and
        He struck Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said to God, \u201CI have sinned greatly because I have
        done this thing. But now, I beseech You, take away the wickedness and guilt
        of Your servant, for I have acted very foolishly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the Lord said to Gad, David\u2019s seer, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGo and tell David, saying, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CI
        offer you three choices; choose for yourself one of them, which I will do
        to you [as punishment for your sin].\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Gad came to David and said to him, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Choose
        for yourself "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "either three years of famine, or three months to be swept away before
        your enemies, while the sword of your enemies overtakes you, or else three
        days of the sword of the Lord and plague in the land, and the angel of the
        Lord bringing destruction throughout all the territory of Israel.\u2019 Now
        therefore, consider what answer I shall return to Him who sent me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "David said to Gad, \u201CI am in great distress; please let me fall
        into the hands of the Lord, for His mercies are very great; but do not let
        me fall into the hand of man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the Lord sent a plague on Israel, and 70,000 men of Israel fell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "God sent an angel to Jerusalem to destroy it; and as he was destroying
        it, the Lord looked, and relented concerning the catastrophe and said to
        the destroying angel, \u201CIt is enough; now remove your hand [of judgment].\u201D
        And the angel of the Lord was standing by the threshing floor of Ornan the
        Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then David raised his eyes and saw the angel of the Lord standing
        between earth and heaven, having a drawn sword in his hand stretched out
        over Jerusalem. Then David and the elders, covered in sackcloth, fell on
        their faces. '
      comments: []
    - name: "17: David\u2019s Altar"
      title: "David\u2019s Altar"
      number: 17
      content: "David said to God, \u201CIs it not I who commanded the people to
        be counted? I am the one who has sinned and done evil; but as for these sheep
        [the people of Israel], what have they done? O Lord my God, please let Your
        hand be against me and my father\u2019s house, but not against Your people
        that they should be plagued.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the angel of the Lord commanded Gad to say to David, that David
        should go up and build an altar to the Lord on the threshing floor of Ornan
        the Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So David went up at Gad\u2019s word, which he spoke in the name of
        the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now Ornan was threshing wheat, and he turned back and saw the angel;
        and his four sons who were with him hid themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'As David came to Ornan, Ornan looked and saw him, and went out from
        the threshing floor and bowed down before David with his face to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then David said to Ornan, \u201CGive me the site of this threshing
        floor, so that I may build an altar on it to the Lord. You shall charge me
        the full price for it, so that the plague may be averted from the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Ornan said to David, \u201CTake it for yourself; and let my lord
        the king do what is good in his eyes. See, I will give you the oxen also
        for burnt offerings and the threshing sledges (heavy wooden platforms) for
        wood and the wheat for the grain offering; I give it all.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But King David said to Ornan, \u201CNo, I will certainly pay the
        full price; for I will not take what is yours for the Lord, nor offer a burnt
        offering which costs me nothing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So David gave Ornan 600 shekels of gold by weight for the site. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then David built an altar to the Lord there and presented burnt offerings
        and peace offerings. And he called on the Lord, and He answered him with
        fire from heaven on the altar of burnt offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then the Lord commanded the [avenging] angel, and he put his sword
        back into its sheath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'At that time, when David saw that the Lord had answered him on the
        threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite, he sacrificed there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For the tabernacle of the Lord, which Moses made in the wilderness,
        and the altar of burnt offering were at that time in the high place at Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But David could not go before it to inquire of God, for he was terrified
        by the sword of the angel of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Prepares for Temple Building'
      title: David Prepares for Temple Building
      number: 1
      content: "  Then David said, \u201CThis is the house of the Lord God, and this
        is the altar of burnt offering for Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David gave orders to gather the foreigners who were in the land
        of Israel, and he assigned stonecutters to hew out stones to build the house
        of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David prepared large quantities of iron to make nails for the doors
        of the gates and for the clamps (trusses), and more bronze than could be
        weighed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and cedar trees beyond number, for the Sidonians and Tyrians brought
        large quantities of cedar timber to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Solomon Charged with the Task'
      title: Solomon Charged with the Task
      number: 5
      content: "David said, \u201CSolomon my son is young and inexperienced, and
        the house that is to be built for the Lord shall be exceedingly magnificent,
        famous, and an object of glory and splendor throughout all lands [of the
        earth]. So now I will make preparations for it.\u201D Therefore, David made
        ample preparations before his death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he called for Solomon his son and ordered him to build a house
        for the Lord, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "David said to Solomon, \u201CMy son, I had intended to build a house
        for the Name (Presence) of the Lord my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But the word of the Lord came to me, saying, \u2018You have shed
        much blood and have waged great wars; you shall not build a house for My
        Name, because you have shed so much blood on the earth before me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Behold, a son will be born to you, who will be a man of peace. I
        will give him rest from all his enemies on every side; for his name shall
        be Solomon, and I will give peace and quiet to Israel in his days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He shall build a house for My Name (Presence). He shall be My son
        and I will be his father; and I will establish his royal throne over Israel
        forever.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now, my son, may the Lord be with you so that you may be successful
        and build the house of the Lord your God, just as He has spoken concerning
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Only may the Lord give you wisdom and understanding, and give you
        charge over Israel, so that you may keep the law of the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then you will prosper, if you are careful to observe and fulfill
        the statutes and ordinances which the Lord commanded Moses concerning Israel.
        Be strong and courageous, do not fear nor be dismayed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now listen, with great trouble I have prepared and provided for the
        house of the Lord 100,000 talents of gold, 1,000,000 talents of silver, and
        bronze and iron beyond weighing, for they are great in quantity. I have also
        prepared and provided timber and stone, and you may add to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Further, you have workmen in abundance: stonecutters and stonemasons
        and carpenters, and all men who are skillful in every kind of work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "As for the gold, the silver, the bronze, and the iron, there is no
        limit. So arise and begin working, and may the Lord be with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'David also commanded all the leaders of Israel to help Solomon his
        son, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIs not the Lord your God with you? And has He not given you
        rest and peace on every side? For He has given the inhabitants of the land
        into my hand, and the land is subdued before the Lord and before His people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now set your heart and your soul to seek (inquire of, require as
        your vital necessity) the Lord your God. Arise and build the sanctuary of
        the Lord God, so that you may bring the ark of the covenant of the Lord and
        the holy articles and utensils of God into the house built for the Name (Presence)
        of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Reigns'
      title: Solomon Reigns
      number: 1
      content: '  When David reached old age, he made his son Solomon king over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Offices of the Levites'
      title: Offices of the Levites
      number: 2
      content: 'And he assembled together all the leaders of Israel with the priests
        and Levites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Levites thirty years old and upward were counted, and their number
        man by man was 38,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Of these 24,000 were to oversee and inspect the work of the house
        of the Lord and 6,000 were to be administrators and judges, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and 4,000 were gatekeepers, and 4,000 [musicians] were to praise
        the Lord with the instruments which David made for giving praise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Gershonites'
      title: Gershonites
      number: 6
      content: 'And David organized them into divisions according to the sons of
        Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Of the Gershonites: Ladan (Libni) and Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The sons of Ladan: Jehiel the first and Zetham and Joel\u2014three
        in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The sons of Shimei: Shelomoth, Haziel, and Haran\u2014three in all.
        These were the heads of the fathers\u2019 households of Ladan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The sons of Shimei: Jahath, Zina (Zizah), Jeush, and Beriah. These
        were the four sons of Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Kohathites'
      title: Kohathites
      number: 11
      content: "Jahath was the first and Zizah the second; but Jeush and Beriah did
        not have many sons [not enough for a father\u2019s house or clan], so they
        were [counted together] as one father\u2019s household, one working group.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel\u2014four in
        all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Amram: Aaron and Moses. Aaron was set apart to consecrate
        him as most holy, he and his sons forever, to burn incense before the Lord,
        attend to His service, and to bless [worshipers] in His name forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But as for Moses the man of God, his sons were counted among the
        tribe of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Moses: Gershom and Eliezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The son of Gershom: Shebuel the chief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The son of Eliezer was Rehabiah the chief. Eliezer had no other sons,
        but Rehabiah\u2019s sons were very many [in number]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The son of Izhar: Shelomith the chief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Hebron: Jeriah the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel
        the third, and Jekameam the fourth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Merarites'
      title: Merarites
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Uzziel: Micah the first and Isshiah the second.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Mahli: Eleazar and
        Kish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Eleazar died and had no sons, but daughters only, and their relatives,
        the sons of Kish, took them as wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Duties Revised'
      title: Duties Revised
      number: 23
      content: "The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jeremoth\u2014three in all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "These were the Levites by their fathers\u2019 households, the heads
        of the fathers\u2019 households of those registered, according to the number
        of names of the individuals who were the servants of the house of the Lord,
        from twenty years old and upward. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For David said, \u201CThe Lord God of Israel, has given peace and
        rest to His people, and He dwells in Jerusalem forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Also, the Levites will no longer need to carry the tabernacle and
        all its utensils for its service.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For by the last words of David, the Levites from twenty years old
        and above were counted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For their duty is to assist [the priests] the sons of Aaron in the
        service of the house of the Lord, in [caring for] the courtyards, the chambers,
        the purifying of all holy things, and any work of the service of the house
        of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and with the showbread, and the fine flour for a grain offering,
        and unleavened wafers, or what is baked in the pan or what is well-mixed,
        and all measures of volume and size [as the Law of Moses required]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'They are to stand every morning to thank and praise the Lord, and
        likewise at evening, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and to offer all burnt sacrifices to the Lord on the Sabbaths, the
        new moons, and the festivals by number according to the ordinance concerning
        them, continually before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: So they shall be responsible for the Tent of Meeting, the Holy Place,
        and the sons of Aaron their relatives, for the service of the house of the
        Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Divisions of Levites'
      title: Divisions of Levites
      number: 1
      content: '  The divisions of the descendants of Aaron were these: the sons
        of Aaron were Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But Nadab and Abihu died before their father and had no sons; therefore
        Eleazar and Ithamar served as priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David, with Zadok of the sons of Eleazar and Ahimelech of the sons
        of Ithamar, divided them according to their offices for their assigned duties. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Since there were more chief men found among the descendants of Eleazar
        than among the descendants of Ithamar [because of Eli\u2019s misfortunes,
        and Saul\u2019s massacre of the priests at Nob], they were divided in this
        way: sixteen heads of fathers\u2019 households of the descendants of Eleazar
        and eight of the descendants of Ithamar, corresponding to their fathers\u2019
        households. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So they were divided by lot, one group with the other; for they were
        officers of the sanctuary and officers (high priests) of God, both from the
        descendants of Eleazar and from the descendants of Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Shemaiah, the son of Nethanel the scribe, from the Levites, recorded
        them in the presence of the king, the officers, Zadok the priest, Ahimelech
        the son of Abiathar [the priest who escaped Saul\u2019s massacre at Nob],
        and the heads of the fathers\u2019 households of the priests and of the Levites;
        one father\u2019s household taken for Eleazar and one taken for Ithamar.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The lots fell, the first one to Jehoiarib, the second to Jedaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the fifth to Malchijah, the sixth to Mijamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the seventh to Hakkoz, the eighth to Abijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the ninth to Jeshua, the tenth to Shecaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the eleventh to Eliashib, the twelfth to Jakim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the thirteenth to Huppah, the fourteenth to Jeshebeab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the fifteenth to Bilgah, the sixteenth to Immer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Happizzez, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the nineteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Jehezkel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the twenty-first to Jachin, the twenty-second to Gamul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the twenty-third to Delaiah, the twenty-fourth to Maaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These were their offices and positions for their service in the house
        of the Lord according to the ordinance given to them by their father (ancestor)
        Aaron, just as the Lord God of Israel had commanded him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now as for the rest of the sons of Levi: of the sons of Amram: Shubael;
        of the sons of Shubael: Jehdeiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Of Rehabiah: of the sons of Rehabiah: Isshiah the first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Of the Izharites: Shelomoth; of the sons of Shelomoth, Jahath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Hebron: Jeriah the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel
        the third, Jekameam the fourth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Of the sons of Uzziel, Micah; of the sons of Micah, Shamir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The brother of Micah, Isshiah; of the sons of Isshiah, Zechariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi; the sons of Jaaziah, Beno. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Merari: by Jaaziah were Beno, Shoham, Zaccur, and Ibri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'By Mahli: Eleazar, who had no sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'By Kish: the sons of Kish, Jerahmeel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jerimoth. These were the sons
        of the Levites according to their fathers\u2019 households. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "These also cast lots as did their relatives the sons of Aaron in
        the presence of David the king, Zadok, Ahimelech, and the heads of the fathers\u2019
        households of the priests and of the Levites\u2014the head of father\u2019s
        households as well as those of his younger brother."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Number and Services of Musicians'
      title: Number and Services of Musicians
      number: 1
      content: '  Moreover, David and the commanders of the army selected for the
        [temple] service some of the sons of Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun, who were
        to prophesy with lyres, harps, and cymbals. The list of the musicians who
        performed their service was as follows:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Of the sons of Asaph: Zaccur, Joseph, Nethaniah, and Asharelah; the
        sons of Asaph were under the direction of Asaph, who prophesied under the
        direction of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Of Jeduthun, the sons of Jeduthun: Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Shimei,
        Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the direction of their father Jeduthun,
        who prophesied with the lyre in thanksgiving and praise to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Of Heman, the sons of Heman: Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel,
        Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, Romamti-ezer, Joshbekashah,
        Mallothi, Hothir, and Mahazioth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "All these [men] were the sons of Heman the king\u2019s seer to exalt
        him in accordance with the words of God; for God gave Heman fourteen sons
        and three daughters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All these were under the direction of their father to sing in the
        house of the Lord, with cymbals, harps, and lyres, for the service of the
        house of God. Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman were under the order and direction
        of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Divisions of Musicians'
      title: Divisions of Musicians
      number: 7
      content: 'So their number [who led the remainder of the 4,000], with their
        relatives who were trained in singing to the Lord, all who were skillful,
        was 288.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The musicians cast lots for their duties, everyone alike, the small
        (younger) as well as the great (older), the teacher as well as the student.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The first lot for Asaph fell to Joseph; the second to Gedaliah, to
        him, his relatives and his sons, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the third to Zaccur, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the fourth to Izri, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the fifth to Nethaniah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the sixth to Bukkiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the seventh to Jesharelah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the eighth to Jeshaiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the ninth to Mattaniah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the tenth to Shimei, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the eleventh to Azarel, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the twelfth to Hashabiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the thirteenth to Shubael, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the fourteenth to Mattithiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'the fifteenth to Jeremoth, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the sixteenth to Hananiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the seventeenth of Joshbekashah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'the eighteenth to Hanani, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'the nineteenth to Mallothi, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the twentieth to Eliathah, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'the twenty-first to Hothir, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'the twenty-second to Giddalti, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'the twenty-third to Mahazioth, his sons and his relatives, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
