      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Divisions of the Gatekeepers'
      title: Divisions of the Gatekeepers
      number: 1
      content: '  For the divisions of the gatekeepers: Of the Korahites: Meshelemiah
        the son of Kore, of the sons of Asaph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Meshelemiah had sons: Zechariah the firstborn, Jediael the second,
        Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Elam the fifth, Jehohanan the sixth, Eliehoenai the seventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Obed-edom had sons: Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second,
        Joah the third, Sacar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, Peullethai the eighth; for
        God had blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Also to his son Shemaiah sons were born who ruled over the house
        of their father, for they were courageous men of ability. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Shemaiah: Othni, Rephael, Obed, and Elzabad, whose brothers
        were courageous and able men, Elihu and Semachiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All these were sons of Obed-edom [in whose house the ark was kept],
        they and their sons and relatives, strong and able men for the service\u2014sixty-two
        from Obed-edom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Meshelemiah had sons and relatives, eighteen courageous men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Also Hosah, one of the sons of Merari, had sons: Shimri the first
        and chief (although he was not the firstborn, his father made him first), '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the third, Zechariah the fourth; the
        sons and relatives of Hosah were thirteen in all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'To these divisions of the gatekeepers, the chief men, were given
        duties, like their relatives, to minister in the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They cast lots, the small (younger) and great (older) alike, in accordance
        with their fathers\u2019 households, for every gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The lot for the east [gates] fell to Shelemiah. They cast lots also
        for his son Zechariah, a wise counselor, and his lot came out for the north
        [gates]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'To Obed-edom [it came out] for the south [gates], and the storehouse
        was allotted to his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'To Shuppim and Hosah [the lot fell] for the west [gates], by the
        gate of Shallecheth, on the ascending highway, division by division. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'On the east were six Levites, on the north four a day, on the south
        four a day, and two by two at the storehouse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'At the colonnade on the west side [of the outer court of the temple]
        there were four at the road and two at the colonnade. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Keepers of the Treasure'
      title: Keepers of the Treasure
      number: 19
      content: 'These were the divisions of the gatekeepers among the Korahites and
        the sons of Merari.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Of the Levites, Ahijah was in charge of the treasuries of the house
        of God and the treasuries of the dedicated gifts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The sons of Ladan, the sons of the Gershonites belonging to Ladan,
        namely, the Jehielites, were the heads of the fathers\u2019 households, belonging
        to Ladan the Gershonite.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Jehieli, Zetham and his brother Joel, were in charge
        of the treasuries of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Of the Amramites, Izharites, Hebronites, and Uzzielites: '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Shebuel the son of Gershom, the son of Moses, was supervisor over
        the treasuries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'His relatives by Eliezer were his son Rehabiah, his son Jeshaiah,
        his son Joram, his son Zichri, and his son Shelomoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "This Shelomoth and his relatives were in charge of all the treasuries
        of the dedicated gifts which King David, the heads of the fathers\u2019 households,
        the commanders of thousands and hundreds, and the commanders of the army,
        had dedicated. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'From spoil won in battles they dedicated gifts to maintain and repair
        the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Outside Duties'
      title: Outside Duties
      number: 28
      content: 'Also all that Samuel the seer had dedicated, and Saul the son of
        Kish, Abner the son of Ner and Joab the son of Zeruiah, everyone who had
        dedicated anything, this was in the care of Shelomoth and his relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Of the Izharites: Chenaniah and his sons were appointed to outside
        duties for Israel, as administrators and judges. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Of the Hebronites: Hashabiah and his relatives, 1,700 capable men,
        were in charge of the affairs of Israel west of the Jordan, for all the work
        of the Lord and the service of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Of the Hebronites: Jerijah was the chief (these Hebronites were examined
        according to their descendants and fathers\u2019 households in the fortieth
        [and final] year of David\u2019s reign, and men of courage and ability were
        found among them at Jazer in Gilead) "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and Jerijah\u2019s relatives, 2,700 capable men, were heads of fathers\u2019
        households; and King David made them overseers of the Reubenites, the Gadites,
        and the half-tribe of Manasseh, for everything pertaining to God and to the
        king."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Commanders of the Army'
      title: Commanders of the Army
      number: 1
      content: "  This is the list of the sons (descendants) of Israel, the heads
        of fathers\u2019 households, the commanders of thousands and of hundreds,
        and their officers who served the king in all matters of the divisions which
        came in and went out month by month throughout the year, each division numbering
        24,000:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jashobeam the son of Zabdiel was in charge of the first division
        for the first month; and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He was descended from Perez, and was chief of all the commanders
        of the army for the first month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Dodai the Ahohite and his division was in charge of the division
        for the second month, Mikloth was the chief officer; and in his division
        were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The third commander of the army for the third month was Benaiah,
        the son of Jehoiada the priest, as chief; and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'This is the Benaiah who was the mighty man of the thirty and was
        in charge of the thirty; and Ammizabad his son was over his division. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The fourth, for the fourth month was Asahel the brother of Joab,
        and Zebadiah his son after him; and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The fifth, for the fifth month was the commander Shamhuth the Izrahite;
        and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sixth, for the sixth month was Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite;
        and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The seventh, for the seventh month was Helez the Pelonite of the
        sons of Ephraim; and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The eighth, for the eighth month was Sibbecai the Hushathite of the
        Zerahites; and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The ninth, for the ninth month was Abiezer of Anathoth, a Benjamite;
        and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The tenth, for the tenth month was Maharai from Netophah of the Zerahites;
        and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The eleventh, for the eleventh month was Benaiah the Pirathonite
        of the sons of Ephraim; and in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Chief Officers of the Tribes'
      title: Chief Officers of the Tribes
      number: 15
      content: 'The twelfth, for the twelfth month was Heldai the Netophathite of
        Othniel; and in his division were 24,000.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now in charge of the tribes of Israel [were the following]: chief
        officer of the Reubenites was Eliezer the son of Zichri; of the Simeonites,
        Shephatiah the son of Maacah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'of Levi, Hashabiah the son of Kemuel; of Aaron, Zadok; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "of Judah, Elihu, one of David\u2019s brothers; of Issachar, Omri
        the son of Michael; "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'of Zebulun, Ishmaiah the son of Obadiah; of Naphtali, Jeremoth the
        son of Azriel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'of the Ephraimites, Hoshea the son of Azaziah; of the half-tribe
        of Manasseh, Joel the son of Pedaiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'of the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead, Iddo the son of Zechariah;
        of Benjamin, Jaasiel the son of Abner; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'of Dan, Azarel the son of Jeroham. These were the leaders of the
        tribes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But David did not count those twenty years of age and under, for
        the Lord had said he would multiply Israel as the stars of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Various Overseers'
      title: Various Overseers
      number: 24
      content: "Joab the son of Zeruiah began a census but did not finish; and because
        of this, [God\u2019s] wrath came on Israel, and the number was not recorded
        in the chronicles of King David.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Azmaveth the son of Adiel was in charge of the king\u2019s storerooms;
        and Jonathan the son of Uzziah was in charge of the storehouses in the country,
        in the cities, in the villages, and in the towers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ezri the son of Chelub was in charge of those who did the work of
        the field, tilling the soil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Shimei the Ramathite was in charge of the vineyards; Zabdi the Shiphmite
        was in charge of the produce of the vineyards for the wine cellars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Baal-hanan the Gederite was in charge of the olive and sycamore trees
        in Shephelah (the lowlands); and Joash was in charge of the stores of [olive]
        oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Shitrai the Sharonite was in charge of the cattle grazing in Sharon;
        Shaphat the son of Adlai was in charge of the cattle in the valleys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Obil the Ishmaelite was in charge of the camels; and Jehdeiah the
        Meronothite was in charge of the donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Counselors'
      title: Counselors
      number: 31
      content: 'Jaziz the Hagrite was in charge of the flocks. All these were overseers
        and stewards of the property which belonged to King David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Also Jonathan, David\u2019s uncle, was a counselor and advisor, a
        man of understanding and wisdom, and a scribe; and Jehiel the son of Hachmoni
        attended (tutored) the king\u2019s sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Ahithophel was counselor to the king; and Hushai the Archite was
        the king\u2019s companion and friend. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Ahithophel was succeeded by Jehoiada the son of Benaiah and by Abiathar;
        and Joab was the commander of the king\u2019s army."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Address about the Temple"
      title: "David\u2019s Address about the Temple"
      number: 1
      content: '  David assembled at Jerusalem all the leaders (officials) of Israel,
        the leaders of the tribes, and the commanders of the divisions that served
        the king, and the commanders of thousands, and the commanders of hundreds,
        and the overseers of all the property and livestock of the king and his sons,
        with the palace officers and the mighty men, and all the brave warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then David the king rose to his feet and said, \u201CHear me, my
        brothers [in arms] and my people. I had intended to build a permanent home
        for the ark of the covenant of the Lord and as a footstool for our God, and
        I prepared materials for the building. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But God said to me, \u2018You shall not build a house for My Name
        (Presence), because you are a man of war and have shed blood.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "However, the Lord, the God of Israel, chose me from all in my father\u2019s
        house to be king over Israel forever. For He has chosen Judah to be the leader;
        and in the house (tribe) of Judah he chose the house of my father; and among
        the sons of my father He was pleased to make me king over all Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Of all my sons (for the Lord has given me many sons) He has chosen
        my son Solomon to sit on the throne of the kingdom of the Lord over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to me, \u2018Solomon your son shall build My house and My
        courts; for I have chosen him to be a son to Me, and I will be a father to
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I will establish his kingdom forever if he loyally and continually
        obeys My commandments and My ordinances, as is done today.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now therefore, in the sight of all Israel, the assembly of the Lord,
        and in the hearing of our God, observe and seek after all the commandments
        of the Lord your God so that you may possess the good land and leave it as
        an inheritance to your sons after you forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAs for you, Solomon my son, know the God of your father [have
        personal knowledge of Him, be acquainted with, and understand Him; appreciate,
        heed, and cherish Him] and serve Him with a blameless heart and a willing
        mind; for the Lord searches all hearts and minds, and understands every intent
        and inclination of the thoughts. If you seek Him [inquiring for and of Him
        and requiring Him as your first and vital necessity] He will let you find
        Him; but if you abandon (turn away from) Him, He will reject you forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Consider this carefully, for the Lord has chosen you to build a house
        for the sanctuary. Be courageous and strong and do it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then David gave to his son Solomon the plan for the porch of the
        temple, its buildings, its treasuries, its upper chambers, its inner rooms,
        and for the place for the [ark and its] mercy seat; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and the plan of all that he had in mind, for the courts of the house
        of the Lord, and for all the surrounding rooms, for the storerooms of the
        house of God and for the storerooms for the dedicated gifts and offerings; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the plan for the divisions of the priests and the Levites and for
        all the work of the service in the house of the Lord and for all the utensils
        for service in the house of the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'for the golden utensils, the weight of gold and silver for all the
        gold and silver articles for every kind of service; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and the weight of gold for the golden lampstands and their golden
        lamps, with the weight of each lampstand and its lamps; and the weight of
        silver for the silver lampstands, with the weight of each lampstand and its
        lamps according to the use of each lampstand; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the gold by weight for each table of showbread, and the silver for
        the tables of silver; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and the forks, the basins, and the pitchers of pure gold; and for
        the golden bowls with the weight for each bowl; and for the silver bowls
        with the weight for each bowl; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and for the altar of incense refined gold by weight; and gold for
        the model of the chariot of the cherubim that spread their wings and covered
        the ark of the Lord\u2019s covenant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAll this,\u201D said David, \u201Cthe Lord made me understand
        in writing by His hand upon me, all the work and details [to be done] according
        to this plan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then David said to his son Solomon, \u201CBe strong and courageous,
        and take action; do not fear nor be dismayed, for the Lord God, my God, is
        with you. He will not fail you nor abandon you [but will guide you in the
        construction] until you have finished all the work for the service of the
        house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And see, [you have] the divisions of the priests and Levites for
        all the service of God\u2019s house, and every willing, skillful man will
        be with you in all the kinds of work for any kind of service. Also the officers
        and all the people will be entirely at your command.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Offerings for the Temple'
      title: Offerings for the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "  And King David said to all the assembly, \u201CMy son Solomon,
        whom alone God has chosen, is still young and inexperienced and the work
        is great; for the temple is not for man but for the Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So with all my ability I have provided for the house of my God the
        gold for the things of gold, silver for the things of silver, bronze for
        the things of bronze, iron for the things of iron, and wood for the things
        of wood, as well as onyx stones and stones to be inlaid, stones of antimony
        (a brittle, silvery-white metal) and stones of various colors, and all kinds
        of precious stones and alabaster in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Moreover, because I delight in the house of my God, the [personal]
        treasure that I have of gold and silver, I give to the house of my God, in
        addition to all that I have already provided for the holy house: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'namely, 3,000 talents of gold from the gold of Ophir, and 7,000 talents
        of refined silver, to overlay the walls of the buildings; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "gold for the things of gold, silver for the things of silver, that
        is, for all the work to be done by craftsmen. Now who is willing to consecrate
        himself today to the Lord?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the rulers of the fathers\u2019 households, and leaders of the
        tribes of Israel, and the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, with the
        overseers of the king\u2019s work, offered willingly "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and gave for the service of the house of God: 5,000 talents and 10,000
        darics of gold, and 10,000 talents of silver, and 18,000 talents of bronze,
        and 100,000 talents of iron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Whoever had precious stones gave them to the treasury of the house
        of the Lord, in the care of Jehiel the Gershonite. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: David\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "David\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the people rejoiced because they had given willingly, for with
        a whole and blameless heart they had offered freely to the Lord. King David
        also rejoiced greatly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore David blessed the Lord in the sight of all the assembly
        and said, \u201CBlessed (praised, adored, and thanked) are You, O Lord God
        of Israel (Jacob) our father, forever and ever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yours, O Lord, is the greatness and the power and the glory and the
        victory and the majesty, indeed everything that is in the heavens and on
        the earth; Yours is the dominion and kingdom, O Lord, and You exalt Yourself
        as head over all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Both riches and honor come from You, and You rule over all. In Your
        hand is power and might; and it is in Your hands to make great and to give
        strength to everyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now therefore, our God, we thank You, and praise Your glorious name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBut who am I, and who are my people, that we should be able
        to offer as generously as this? For all things come from You, and from Your
        own hand we have given to You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For we are sojourners before You, and tenants, as all our fathers
        were; our days on the earth are like a shadow, and there is no hope [of remaining]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O Lord our God, all this abundance that we have prepared to build
        You a house for Your holy Name, it is from Your hand, and is all Your own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I know also, my God, that You test the heart and delight in uprightness
        and integrity. In the uprightness of my heart I have willingly offered all
        these things. So now with joy I have seen Your people who are present here,
        make their offerings willingly and freely to You. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O Lord, God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, our fathers, keep forever
        such purposes and thoughts in the minds of Your people, and direct their
        hearts toward You; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and give to my son Solomon a perfect heart to keep Your commandments,
        Your testimonies, and Your statutes, and to do all [that is necessary] to
        build the temple [for You], for which I have made provision.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Sacrifices'
      title: Sacrifices
      number: 20
      content: "Then David said to all the assembly, \u201CNow bless (praise, thank)
        the Lord your God.\u201D And all the assembly blessed the Lord, the God of
        their fathers, and bowed down and honored the Lord and the king [as His earthly
        representative].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The next day they offered sacrifices and burnt offerings to the Lord:
        1,000 bulls, 1,000 rams, and 1,000 lambs, with their drink offerings (libations)
        and sacrifices in abundance for all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Solomon Again Made King'
      title: Solomon Again Made King
      number: 22
      content: 'They ate and drank that day before the Lord with great rejoicing. 
        They made Solomon the son of David king a second time, and anointed him as
        ruler for the Lord and Zadok as [high] priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Solomon sat on the throne of the Lord as king in place of David
        his father; and he prospered, and all Israel obeyed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'All of the leaders and warriors, and also all the sons of King David,
        pledged allegiance to King Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The Lord highly exalted Solomon in the sight of all Israel, and bestowed
        on him royal majesty which had not been on any king before him in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Thus David the son of Jesse reigned over all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Death of David'
      title: Death of David
      number: 27
      content: 'The time that he reigned over Israel was forty years; he reigned
        seven years in Hebron and thirty-three years in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He died in a good old age [his seventy-first year], full of days
        (satisfied), riches and honor. Solomon his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now the acts of King David, from first to last, are written in the
        chronicles (records) of Samuel the seer, in the chronicles of Nathan the
        prophet, and in the chronicles of Gad the seer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: with [accounts of] all his reign, and his power, and the times and
        circumstances which came on him, on Israel, and on all the kingdoms of the
        [surrounding] lands.
      comments: []
